s:1234:"<p>Using extended character sets in Zen Grid Framework v4 themes is possible by simply using the code provided in the quick use page for your selected Google font.</p>
<p>The screenshot below highlights the code required to apply the Vietnamese character set for the Roboto font.</p>
<p><img src="/zgf4-docs/images/documentation/fonts/extended-font.png" alt="Extended Character Sets" /></p>
<p>The code required is:</p>
<pre><code>Roboto&amp;subset=latin,vietnamese</code></pre>
<p>This needs to be added to the font option as per the screenshot below:</p>
<p><img src="/zgf4-docs/images/documentation/fonts/extended-setting.png" alt="extended-setting" /></p>
<p>The font file is then loaded via this href link:</p>
<pre><code>&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="//fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto&amp;subset=latin,vietnamese" type="text/css" /&gt;</code></pre>
<p>And the following css is embedded into the page:</p>
<pre><code>html &gt; body {font-family: 'Roboto'}</code></pre>
<p>Now if we add a sample of Vietnamese Lorem Ipsum in the page you can see the text is rendered using the extended characters for the Vietnamese language.</p>
<p><img src="/zgf4-docs/images/documentation/fonts/viet-sample.png" alt="Vietnamese" /></p>";